{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"RELATED LIVE OBSERVATION (code-review gate, not just plan-review). The Gerrit review-bot cast LLM-Review-1 on change 223 (a clean, CI-green config-check change) with message '[LLM-Review: BLOCK — finding] rebar code review found 0 blocking issue(s):' — a BLOCK with reason 'finding' and ZERO blocking findings. Investigation of whether the known verify-budget-exhaustion fix (ticket 59bc: commits 964791dd8 2026-06-28 + 314e4191c 2026-06-29, both on main; touches gate_dispatch.py/orchestrator.py/runner.py — the kernel SHARED with code-review) was deployed:\n- The running review-bot image was BUILT 2026-07-02T20:31 — AFTER the 59bc fix landed — and the deployed package contains the budget/length guard. So THE FIX IS DEPLOYED; this -1 is NOT a 'fix-not-deployed' case.\n- Therefore the fix did NOT prevent this -1. Signature differs from a budget coverage-gap: reason='finding' (not 'coverage-gap (llm-unavailable/...)'), so it is NOT classified by _coverage_gap_reason. This looks like a DISTINCT-but-related verdict-consistency defect on the CODE-REVIEW path: the four-pass gate returns a non-PASS verdict with an empty blocking[] and no coverage-gap, which the adapter maps to _block('finding', verdict) -> a false -1 with '0 blocking issues'. Root-cause should cover BOTH the plan-review verify-truncation (this bug's original scope) AND this code-review non-PASS-with-0-findings mapping (adapter._block / _coverage_gap_reason should treat 'non-PASS with 0 findings and no gap' as a coverage-gap/INDETERMINATE, never a 'finding' BLOCK).\n(Aside: the bot's journald is ALSO full of 409 'Revision has more than 1 parent' on merge changes — the deployed bot is pre-S2, so it cannot review merges. THAT is a genuine staleness case motivating the auto-deploy story 8903, distinct from this code bug.)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783104184163382001,"uuid":"4d1a2009-94aa-4535-81db-ee5f6f804f74"}